    All address components in separate properties. For each property the intention is to have a full name, e.g. "New York", and an abbreviated name, e.g. "NY". Though note that as of May 2013, Google Places data often provides the same value for both properties. Typically this is the full name, though for countries and states/provinces it is often the abbreviated name. Properties will be null when the value is not available.
